WEBVTT

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:06.580
I want you to draw Mr. Braun's attention,

00:00:06.580 --> 00:00:10.360
so he doesn't notice any 
shaking from the experiment.

00:00:10.360 --> 00:00:11.790
Got it!

00:00:11.790 --> 00:00:13.880
I'll just have to seduce him.

00:00:13.880 --> 00:00:14.790
Want to touch it?

00:00:14.790 --> 00:00:16.230
It's pretty firm.

00:00:16.230 --> 00:00:17.440
It is.

00:00:17.440 --> 00:00:18.210
Right?

00:00:18.210 --> 00:00:19.450
Leave it to me.

00:00:19.450 --> 00:00:20.740
You're seducing him, right?

00:00:20.740 --> 00:00:21.930
Yup, what about it?

00:00:21.930 --> 00:00:23.340
Never mind. I'm counting on you.

00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.770
Okey-dokey.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:32.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:35.710
Now!

00:00:35.710 --> 00:00:36.720
Assistant, go!

00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:39.100
What?

00:00:42.240 --> 00:00:44.140
Oh, no... I failed.

00:00:44.140 --> 00:00:46.850
How many times do I have to tell you?

00:00:51.420 --> 00:00:52.600
It stopped?

00:00:53.190 --> 00:00:54.220
My assistant?

00:00:54.220 --> 00:00:55.270
No...

00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:09.530
What is this?

00:01:09.530 --> 00:01:10.640
No way!

00:01:14.180 --> 00:01:15.950
What do you mean...

00:01:17.570 --> 00:01:19.440
"No way"?

00:02:50.950 --> 00:02:55.930
Dogma in Event Horizon

00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:57.680
In other words,

00:02:57.680 --> 00:03:00.610
the 42" CRT on the first floor

00:03:00.610 --> 00:03:03.180
just happens to function as the lifter.

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:05.710
So we were only able to send

00:03:05.710 --> 00:03:10.110
D-mail when the studio was open 
and the TV was on...

00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:12.080
That makes a lot of sense!

00:03:12.080 --> 00:03:14.820
Don't be so loud. It hurts my head...

00:03:14.820 --> 00:03:15.850
Are you okay?

00:03:15.850 --> 00:03:18.200
Mr. Braun...

00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:21.290
I never thought you would resort to violence.

00:03:21.290 --> 00:03:23.870
In a way, it's your own fault.

00:03:23.870 --> 00:03:26.580
You're the one who wanted to run an experiment!

00:03:27.430 --> 00:03:30.460
Anyway, we almost completely understand

00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:32.000
how the Phone Microwave works now.

00:03:32.870 --> 00:03:34.250
Which means that next...

00:03:34.250 --> 00:03:37.750
We should consider physically transporting 
an object through time.

00:03:37.750 --> 00:03:38.560
Impossible.

00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:40.180
Don't dismiss it so quickly!

00:03:40.600 --> 00:03:43.420
It's going to end up jelly, no matter what we do.

00:03:43.420 --> 00:03:47.020
And how the heck do you 
fit a human into 36 bytes...

00:03:50.340 --> 00:03:51.900
Is this really the time for showing off?

00:03:51.900 --> 00:03:54.050
Why would I want to show off to you?

00:03:54.050 --> 00:03:55.770
Look at the title of my paper.

00:03:57.630 --> 00:03:59.800
"The Analysis of Nerve Pulse Signals

00:03:59.800 --> 00:04:02.830
Stored in Memory Within the Temporal Lobe."

00:04:02.830 --> 00:04:04.930
Can I get that in Japanese?

00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:08.550
Essentially, it has to do with people's memories.

00:04:08.550 --> 00:04:10.810
I majored in neuroscience.

00:04:11.470 --> 00:04:13.040
Put simply,

00:04:13.040 --> 00:04:17.270
the brain stores memories as pulse signals.

00:04:17.270 --> 00:04:19.410
They're a type of electrical data.

00:04:19.410 --> 00:04:21.890
Data... You can't mean...

00:04:21.890 --> 00:04:23.110
That's right.

00:04:23.110 --> 00:04:26.540
Sending a human through time is impossible,

00:04:26.540 --> 00:04:29.770
but it might be possible to send their memory data.

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:31.950
Me on 2010/8/13 AD                    Hippocampus

00:04:30.040 --> 00:04:31.330
Where?

00:04:31.330 --> 00:04:33.090
To the you in the past.

00:04:31.950 --> 00:04:37.270
Scan Memory Data (3.24T)
Nerve Pulse Signals  -->  Encode to Electric Signals

00:04:33.090 --> 00:04:34.570
We turn the memories into data,

00:04:34.570 --> 00:04:37.150
and we send them back, 
the same way as with the D-mail.

00:04:37.150 --> 00:04:42.400
Basically, you're transplanting your 
present brain's contents into the past.

00:04:37.270 --> 00:04:40.390
Time Leap Machine

00:04:40.390 --> 00:04:43.200
Time Leap! 
(Same as D-Mail)

00:04:42.400 --> 00:04:44.930
In other words, "you" go back to the past!

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:44.930
Me on 2010/8/11 AD 
Overwrite Memory Data!                     Receive

00:04:44.930 --> 00:04:48.200
It's more of a time leap than time travel.

00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:49.880
It's me.

00:04:50.560 --> 00:04:53.220
All the lines have converged at one point.

00:04:53.220 --> 00:04:56.020
The plan will now enter its final stages.

00:04:57.720 --> 00:04:59.620
The goddess who rules the present...

00:05:00.040 --> 00:05:01.970
Begin Operation Verdandi!

00:05:02.390 --> 00:05:03.540
Begin what now?

00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:05.850
Explain what you're talking about a little.

00:05:06.690 --> 00:05:09.600
I'm saying we're going to do that 
time leap you're talking about.

00:05:09.600 --> 00:05:10.610
Begin now.

00:05:10.610 --> 00:05:14.790
But we'll need a lot of stuff to do it.

00:05:14.790 --> 00:05:20.350
Of course, we only have to read 
memories stored in the temporal lobe,

00:05:20.350 --> 00:05:22.920
so I think I can get everything in Akiba...

00:05:24.290 --> 00:05:25.350
But...

00:05:26.200 --> 00:05:27.220
What's wrong?

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:29.680
One problem is that

00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:32.120
I don't think the Phone Microwave will be able

00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:34.970
to sufficiently compress the memory data.

00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:36.760
And...

00:05:37.720 --> 00:05:38.570
What?

00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:40.910
Nothing.

00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:42.540
All right.

00:05:42.540 --> 00:05:45.430
I'll make a list of parts I need for now.

00:05:46.990 --> 00:05:49.970
It's too hard for Mayushii to understand it at all.

00:05:49.970 --> 00:05:52.850
Christina just explained it.

00:05:52.850 --> 00:05:56.850
You're sending your mind, 
as it exists right now, to the past.

00:05:58.850 --> 00:06:01.100
Sounds scary.

00:06:02.040 --> 00:06:04.600
Is the D-mail not good enough?

00:06:04.600 --> 00:06:08.470
There are too many 
chaotic variables with the D-mail.

00:06:08.810 --> 00:06:12.680
One message can change 
things you'd never expect.

00:06:13.680 --> 00:06:16.350
But it's okay to send memories into the past?

00:06:16.350 --> 00:06:19.050
If nothing else, you can

00:06:19.050 --> 00:06:21.500
prevent the past from changing, to a degree.

00:06:22.010 --> 00:06:24.660
You wouldn't have the 
entire city of Akiba changing...

00:06:25.310 --> 00:06:26.350
The city?

00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:29.930
Nothing, never mind.

00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:31.240
Huh?

00:06:31.240 --> 00:06:33.550
But what happens to you

00:06:33.550 --> 00:06:36.280
after you send your memories?

00:06:36.280 --> 00:06:39.120
Your body is still here, isn't it?

00:06:39.930 --> 00:06:41.140
Well...

00:06:41.140 --> 00:06:46.250
So, Mayushii is talking to Okarin now, right?

00:06:47.170 --> 00:06:50.260
Then, you're saying Mayushii goes back a week,

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:53.050
and then relives the week, right?

00:06:53.050 --> 00:06:57.640
What happens if she doesn't talk to Okarin this time?

00:06:57.640 --> 00:07:02.710
I assume that you would recall that we spoke,

00:07:02.710 --> 00:07:04.770
but the fact of our having spoken would be erased.

00:07:04.770 --> 00:07:09.120
In other words, Mayushii would remember us talking,

00:07:09.120 --> 00:07:11.970
but Okarin wouldn't?

00:07:12.680 --> 00:07:14.200
I'd imagine so.

00:07:14.200 --> 00:07:18.140
Then, that's kind of sad.

00:07:20.590 --> 00:07:21.270
For me?

00:07:22.300 --> 00:07:23.290
Nope.

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:26.970
For Mayushii.

00:07:27.830 --> 00:07:30.250
It's Moeka-san!

00:07:30.250 --> 00:07:32.200
Moeka-san!

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:48.770
You look rather unhappy, Shining Finger.

00:07:55.140 --> 00:07:57.140
"Did you get rid of the time machine?"

00:07:57.140 --> 00:07:59.210
We're still using it.

00:07:59.210 --> 00:08:02.480
And now, we might be able to do a time leap—

00:08:02.480 --> 00:08:04.090
Don't tell her about that!

00:08:05.380 --> 00:08:08.060
But Moeka-san's a lab member, too, right?

00:08:08.060 --> 00:08:10.290
She is, but...

00:08:11.710 --> 00:08:13.470
"What's a time leap?"

00:08:15.060 --> 00:08:16.680
Just what it sounds like!

00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:19.320
We can send memories through time.

00:08:19.320 --> 00:08:20.530
Memories...

00:08:23.070 --> 00:08:24.720
Moeka-san?

00:08:29.560 --> 00:08:31.270
Moeka-san!

00:08:31.920 --> 00:08:33.830
Is she okay?

00:08:37.890 --> 00:08:41.260
It would be faster to head for Akibaoo first, I guess?

00:08:41.260 --> 00:08:42.680
Mayuri-oneechan!

00:08:45.820 --> 00:08:48.310
It's Nae-chan!

00:08:48.310 --> 00:08:49.550
What's wrong?

00:08:49.550 --> 00:08:51.230
Yo.

00:08:51.230 --> 00:08:52.930
You're still dressed like that?

00:08:54.650 --> 00:08:58.070
The boss told me to stay this way all day.

00:08:58.070 --> 00:09:00.140
You'll poison children's minds.

00:09:00.140 --> 00:09:00.890
Poison?

00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:03.740
I'm careful never to walk around with poison.

00:09:03.740 --> 00:09:04.690
Huh?

00:09:04.690 --> 00:09:07.000
Anyway, Nae said she wanted to

00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:10.220
talk to Okabe Rintarou, so we were looking for you.

00:09:10.680 --> 00:09:11.560
To me?

00:09:13.500 --> 00:09:14.840
I'm sorry!

00:09:14.840 --> 00:09:17.560
My dad was really mean back there!

00:09:17.770 --> 00:09:19.070
Nae-chan...

00:09:19.070 --> 00:09:21.230
You came all this way to say that?

00:09:21.230 --> 00:09:23.590
What a well-trained little pet.

00:09:23.590 --> 00:09:25.810
She's not a pet.

00:09:26.530 --> 00:09:27.890
Don't worry.

00:09:27.890 --> 00:09:30.660
I cause trouble for Mr. Braun all the time.

00:09:31.070 --> 00:09:31.810
We're even.

00:09:33.470 --> 00:09:36.230
That's not like the Okabe Rintarou I know...

00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:39.470
Okarin's always like this.

00:09:41.430 --> 00:09:44.100
Mayushii's gonna get going, okay?

00:09:44.670 --> 00:09:45.570
Meeting someone?

00:09:45.570 --> 00:09:46.290
Yup!

00:09:46.290 --> 00:09:49.350
I'm going to give the cosplayer, Fubuki-chan, her outfit.

00:09:49.350 --> 00:09:51.220
Come to think of it, it's almost time for Comima.

00:09:51.430 --> 00:09:52.100
Yup.

00:09:52.100 --> 00:09:53.100
Bye!

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:54.850
See you, Suzu-san and Nae-chan!

00:09:56.180 --> 00:09:57.290
See you!

00:09:58.270 --> 00:10:00.460
Okay, let's head back ourselves.

00:10:00.460 --> 00:10:04.390
No, I need to find the parts Christina asked me for.

00:10:06.800 --> 00:10:10.540
Makise Kurisu works with SERN.

00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:23.430
<i>A SERN spy?</i>

00:10:24.610 --> 00:10:25.810
<i>No way.</i>

00:10:31.870 --> 00:10:32.710
All your base are...

00:10:32.710 --> 00:10:33.530
...belong to us.

00:10:37.310 --> 00:10:38.570
You can't sneak up on me!

00:10:38.570 --> 00:10:39.410
It's against the rules!

00:10:40.130 --> 00:10:42.680
So, you were posting on @channel.

00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:46.960
I realized you were an @channeler a long time ago.

00:10:44.240 --> 00:10:45.900
I wasn't, no...

00:10:46.960 --> 00:10:47.890
No!

00:10:47.890 --> 00:10:50.420
There's no point in hiding it now.

00:10:51.220 --> 00:10:52.620
This sucks...

00:10:52.620 --> 00:10:53.600
All right.

00:10:53.600 --> 00:10:54.720
From now on,

00:10:54.720 --> 00:10:56.890
I officially give you the title of Channeler...

00:10:56.890 --> 00:10:59.300
Don't give me any more weird nicknames!

00:10:59.300 --> 00:11:01.280
And please, keep this a secret!

00:11:01.280 --> 00:11:02.270
Why?

00:11:02.730 --> 00:11:05.270
You could list it on your resume.

00:11:05.270 --> 00:11:08.520
If they knew a serious academic were posting,

00:11:08.520 --> 00:11:10.480
they'd probably make a few threads about you.

00:11:10.480 --> 00:11:11.520
Why would I care?

00:11:11.760 --> 00:11:15.960
Then what? You'd sage them?

00:11:17.140 --> 00:11:19.650
I hate myself for understanding that last sentence.

00:11:19.650 --> 00:11:21.520
Either way, I feel better.

00:11:21.520 --> 00:11:22.350
I can't imagine

00:11:22.350 --> 00:11:25.540
anyone who's so terrible at hiding things

00:11:25.540 --> 00:11:26.880
being a spy.

00:11:27.670 --> 00:11:28.520
What does that mean?

00:11:28.820 --> 00:11:33.410
The part-time warrior said you were a SERN spy.

00:11:33.410 --> 00:11:35.600
What is that supposed to mean?

00:11:36.160 --> 00:11:37.860
That's impossible.

00:11:37.860 --> 00:11:39.180
Indeed.

00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:43.390
You're an agent the Organization sent,

00:11:43.390 --> 00:11:46.950
who's had a change of heart 
and now works as my assistant.

00:11:46.950 --> 00:11:48.040
That's not true, either.

00:11:48.040 --> 00:11:50.880
So how's the work going?

00:11:50.880 --> 00:11:51.560
Work?

00:11:52.090 --> 00:11:53.420
The time leap.

00:11:53.420 --> 00:11:55.160
I bought all the parts.

00:11:55.160 --> 00:11:57.440
Oh... That's right.

00:11:57.440 --> 00:11:59.060
I should make it, shouldn't I?

00:12:00.130 --> 00:12:01.770
I've come this far.

00:12:01.770 --> 00:12:03.650
What is this?

00:12:04.300 --> 00:12:05.660
You're getting scared?

00:12:05.660 --> 00:12:07.370
That, too...

00:12:07.370 --> 00:12:11.140
I keep asking myself what will happen 
if we really make it.

00:12:11.680 --> 00:12:13.590
But more than that...

00:12:14.470 --> 00:12:15.460
What?

00:12:15.460 --> 00:12:17.570
I should tell you...

00:12:17.570 --> 00:12:20.100
It seems like it's half-obvious already.

00:12:23.950 --> 00:12:25.860
I can't do it here!

00:12:25.860 --> 00:12:27.850
Let's go somewhere I can't see your face.

00:12:31.680 --> 00:12:36.800
I've got a problem with my dad...

00:12:36.800 --> 00:12:39.700
So your father was struck by lightning,

00:12:39.700 --> 00:12:41.840
on the grassy plains of Arkansas, 
and fell to the dark side—

00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:43.750
If you're going to be a jerk, I'm not telling you.

00:12:43.750 --> 00:12:46.060
All right. Tell me.

00:12:46.720 --> 00:12:49.630
To put it simply, my dad doesn't like me.

00:12:50.470 --> 00:12:52.710
No... He hates me.

00:12:53.320 --> 00:12:57.810
And not as his daughter. As a scientist, as a rival.

00:12:58.540 --> 00:13:01.480
My dad was a physicist.

00:13:01.480 --> 00:13:03.600
I always liked hearing him

00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:07.310
talk about the details of his work.

00:13:07.840 --> 00:13:10.350
And so, by the end of elementary school,

00:13:10.350 --> 00:13:12.720
I could understand his papers.

00:13:14.690 --> 00:13:17.500
And then, I started writing my own papers,

00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:19.180
and winning awards.

00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:23.230
But I didn't care about the awards.

00:13:23.230 --> 00:13:26.340
I loved debating with my father.

00:13:27.190 --> 00:13:29.730
We exchanged papers by e-mail,

00:13:29.730 --> 00:13:31.370
and our debates got deeper.

00:13:32.210 --> 00:13:33.230
But...

00:13:34.470 --> 00:13:37.810
Eventually, my dad stopped debating with me.

00:13:38.910 --> 00:13:41.240
While I enjoyed the debates,

00:13:41.240 --> 00:13:43.290
I was also winning them.

00:13:45.030 --> 00:13:47.200
I pointed out mistakes he'd made,

00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:51.360
and without even thinking about it, I hurt his pride.

00:13:54.460 --> 00:13:56.970
My dad started taking it out on my mom.

00:13:56.970 --> 00:13:58.120
He lost confidence,

00:13:58.120 --> 00:14:00.550
and began withdrawing from his academic peers.

00:14:01.800 --> 00:14:03.940
The last time I saw him,

00:14:03.940 --> 00:14:05.640
he said this to me...

00:14:06.510 --> 00:14:08.660
"Do you pity me?

00:14:08.660 --> 00:14:10.290
Do you look down on me?"

00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:13.510
"You're my daughter. How dare you."

00:14:21.350 --> 00:14:25.370
If I make a device that enables a time leap,

00:14:25.370 --> 00:14:28.430
I think my dad might go insane.

00:14:28.430 --> 00:14:29.910
Even more than before...

00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:32.750
So that's why you're hesitant to make it?

00:14:32.750 --> 00:14:34.230
But don't worry.

00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:37.180
I'll end up doing it, regardless.

00:14:37.180 --> 00:14:39.180
Just like you said, I love experimenting.

00:14:39.700 --> 00:14:42.630
If I see a possibility, I have to investigate it.

00:14:43.860 --> 00:14:45.590
Just like my dad used to...

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:49.180
The time I spent with my dad...

00:14:50.440 --> 00:14:51.680
...was like that.

00:15:04.190 --> 00:15:08.670
Then we begin Operation Verdandi immediately!

00:15:08.670 --> 00:15:10.340
There's no time to waste!

00:15:10.340 --> 00:15:13.270
The Organization stands at our very doorstep!

00:15:13.270 --> 00:15:14.810
That's your response?

00:15:14.810 --> 00:15:16.290
Of course...

00:15:16.290 --> 00:15:17.950
I am Hououin Kyouma.

00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:20.920
I have a destiny to change the world!

00:15:21.940 --> 00:15:23.690
I shouldn't have said anything...

00:15:23.690 --> 00:15:26.040
And we'll reconcile you with your dad, too!

00:15:26.040 --> 00:15:27.800
Where is he?

00:15:28.300 --> 00:15:29.770
H-He's in Aomori.

00:15:29.770 --> 00:15:32.640
We'll need money to go...

00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:33.860
When you work out the time,

00:15:33.860 --> 00:15:35.820
tell me as soon as you can.

00:15:35.820 --> 00:15:38.550
You can't mean to go with me.

00:15:38.550 --> 00:15:39.770
Naturally!

00:15:40.050 --> 00:15:45.270
I need you in peak mental condition, 
so you can further my ambitions!

00:15:45.680 --> 00:15:48.350
I, Hououin Kyouma, shall accompany you.

00:15:48.350 --> 00:15:51.710
And I shall use my masterful people skills

00:15:51.710 --> 00:15:54.510
to reunite father and daughter.

00:15:54.510 --> 00:15:56.230
What?

00:15:56.230 --> 00:15:59.160
You're a self-proclaimed mad scientist, right?

00:15:59.160 --> 00:16:01.400
Since when do mad scientists have people skills?

00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:03.980
Well, um, you see...

00:16:05.630 --> 00:16:06.830
Why are you laughing?

00:16:07.420 --> 00:16:09.990
Sometimes you're a good guy, you know?

00:16:09.990 --> 00:16:11.640
That's the problem.

00:16:11.640 --> 00:16:14.670
Now that you understand 
my greatness, back to work.

00:16:15.220 --> 00:16:16.250
Right, right!

00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:18.630
Just so we're clear, this is now decided.

00:16:18.630 --> 00:16:20.810
So I'm dragging you with me,
whether you want to go or not!

00:16:23.040 --> 00:16:24.740
Sounds good to me.

00:16:31.690 --> 00:16:33.520
Mayuri-chan?

00:16:34.890 --> 00:16:37.300
What's with all this stuff?

00:16:37.300 --> 00:16:40.240
Shouldn't you call that Okarin guy?

00:16:40.240 --> 00:16:41.890
It's okay...

00:16:42.580 --> 00:16:44.890
I'm almost there.

00:16:45.600 --> 00:16:47.490
Look at the label!

00:16:47.490 --> 00:16:49.600
It says "Makise" right here!

00:16:49.600 --> 00:16:52.140
It reads "Makise pudding."

00:16:52.140 --> 00:16:53.340
That's just a brand name,

00:16:53.340 --> 00:16:55.340
like Morinaga pudding or Koiwai pudding.

00:16:55.340 --> 00:16:56.600
Don't play stupid!

00:16:56.600 --> 00:16:58.450
Who's "Makise," anyway?

00:16:58.450 --> 00:16:59.680
That's my name!

00:16:59.680 --> 00:17:01.580
"Christina Makise"?

00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:04.480
If only you'd written "Christina" instead,

00:17:04.480 --> 00:17:07.180
I wouldn't have accidentally 
ingested the extra calories.

00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:09.350
Don't eat other people's food!

00:17:09.350 --> 00:17:12.410
And that's my spoon! Don't use it!

00:17:12.410 --> 00:17:16.110
You use the lab's forks, don't you?!

00:17:16.620 --> 00:17:17.600
I'm here...

00:17:20.200 --> 00:17:21.430
What's all that?

00:17:21.430 --> 00:17:25.230
Mayushii's cosplay materials and sleepover set!

00:17:25.750 --> 00:17:26.810
Sleepover?

00:17:27.420 --> 00:17:28.570
Yup!

00:17:28.570 --> 00:17:30.770
I'm going to make some 
cosplay outfits for Comima.

00:17:30.770 --> 00:17:33.070
Are you sure?

00:17:33.070 --> 00:17:34.220
What about your parents?

00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:35.990
I told them about it.

00:17:35.990 --> 00:17:37.910
You're staying over, too, right?

00:17:37.910 --> 00:17:39.630
To work on the Phone Microwave?

00:17:40.240 --> 00:17:43.460
Yeah, I thought I might.

00:17:43.460 --> 00:17:46.080
But it's kind of depressing to be here.

00:17:46.080 --> 00:17:47.600
There's this Hououin something guy

00:17:47.600 --> 00:17:49.600
who goes around eating people's pudding.

00:17:50.370 --> 00:17:52.110
It's Hououin Kyouma!

00:17:52.110 --> 00:17:53.460
Learn my name, already!

00:17:53.460 --> 00:17:54.930
You're the last person I want to hear that from!

00:17:54.930 --> 00:17:56.910
And don't ignore the part about the pudding!

00:17:56.910 --> 00:17:58.920
Maybe I should leave?

00:17:59.600 --> 00:18:02.140
No, I'll stay,

00:18:02.140 --> 00:18:04.180
but if I do, then Okabe should leave.

00:18:04.910 --> 00:18:05.930
What?!

00:18:06.450 --> 00:18:09.240
The lab is the house of my soul!

00:18:09.240 --> 00:18:10.430
I could never leave—

00:18:12.680 --> 00:18:16.100
Why is her condition for staying that I go shopping?

00:18:16.100 --> 00:18:17.500
Come to think of it,

00:18:17.500 --> 00:18:19.890
I've been running errands 
for my assistant since yesterday.

00:18:22.690 --> 00:18:24.220
Christina?

00:18:24.220 --> 00:18:26.970
From: Assistant 
Subject: I demand compensation and an apology 
I demand two puddings, 
as punishment for the one you ate. And... 
We're taking a late bus to Aomori, 
due to finances.

00:18:28.770 --> 00:18:30.640
"What are you so happy about?

00:18:30.640 --> 00:18:33.970
Don't forget your role as a lab member."

00:18:36.950 --> 00:18:39.060
I'm not happy, stupid!

00:18:39.900 --> 00:18:40.850
What?

00:18:41.400 --> 00:18:43.130
It's nothing!

00:18:43.130 --> 00:18:46.320
Let's get in, before Okabe gets back.

00:18:46.320 --> 00:18:47.350
Okay.

00:18:53.440 --> 00:18:54.600
My assistant again?

00:18:58.180 --> 00:19:01.390
You know too much.

00:19:04.570 --> 00:19:05.640
What?

00:19:26.720 --> 00:19:27.520
Mayuri...

00:19:31.100 --> 00:19:31.890
Mayuri!

00:19:33.310 --> 00:19:34.370
Mayuri!

00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:25.350
I'll never forgive you! Ever!

00:20:25.350 --> 00:20:30.640
Okarin, Mayushii is very sad 
and very embarrassed.

00:20:30.640 --> 00:20:31.930
Jeez!

00:20:31.930 --> 00:20:35.450
Not only did you peep on us in the shower, 
you forgot all the shopping!

00:20:35.460 --> 00:20:37.640
I can't believe it!

00:20:39.120 --> 00:20:39.970
Hey, Okabe!

00:20:39.970 --> 00:20:41.410
Okarin?

00:20:43.960 --> 00:20:44.810
It's Daru-kun!

00:20:45.300 --> 00:20:46.320
What's wrong?

00:20:46.320 --> 00:20:47.510
Why are you here so late?

00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:51.270
I knew it.

00:20:51.800 --> 00:20:53.620
When I accessed it from the outside,

00:20:53.620 --> 00:20:55.810
I thought there was something weird.

00:20:55.810 --> 00:20:57.180
Is something wrong?

00:20:57.180 --> 00:21:01.330
The lab is connected directly to the heart of SERN.

00:21:01.330 --> 00:21:02.420
SERN?

00:21:02.420 --> 00:21:04.190
You've taken over their system?

00:21:04.190 --> 00:21:05.520
I guess so. I win the internet!

00:21:05.950 --> 00:21:07.790
Or so I'd like to say,

00:21:07.790 --> 00:21:10.930
but to be honest, I was connected 
before I even knew it.

00:21:10.930 --> 00:21:12.940
SERN's been standing naked, outside my house,

00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:14.560
this whole time.

00:21:14.560 --> 00:21:15.390
Say what now?

00:21:15.390 --> 00:21:16.750
Wait!

00:21:16.750 --> 00:21:19.370
If we're connected, 
without our having done anything,

00:21:19.370 --> 00:21:21.850
doesn't that imply that they've found us out,

00:21:21.850 --> 00:21:24.810
and are connecting to us?

00:21:25.770 --> 00:21:29.430
Hmm... But I don't think I've made any errors 
that would have gotten us caught.

00:21:30.240 --> 00:21:33.430
Now we can use the LHC all we want.

00:21:31.540 --> 00:21:32.720
<i>It can't be...</i>

00:21:33.430 --> 00:21:35.180
SERN!

00:21:33.430 --> 00:21:35.180
The LHC?

00:21:40.770 --> 00:21:41.930
Okarin?

00:21:46.440 --> 00:21:48.040
Is something wrong with your phone?

00:21:50.320 --> 00:21:51.210
No...

00:21:52.340 --> 00:21:53.520
Nothing.

00:21:54.305 --> 00:22:54.604
Do you want subtitles for any video?
